texts.text:
*Groan*
This trail's so draining...
Would you like me to carry you, Ririn?
What?! There's no way I'm being carried away by some gorilla!
I see... But please feel free to ask if you do feel too tired!
Okay, thanks. I appreciate the offer.
This dam's deep in the mountains, so we just have to keep going.
Yo, hold up. We ain't alone.
Is that...?
An army of demons?
A herd of demons?
Yes, as if they've gathered to discuss something. It could be an army...
Nah, they look way more organized than that...
Yo, it could be an army.
Who goes there?!
Shit, they found us!
Who are you? What are you doing here?
No, your kind has no business being here!
Have you discovered Vritra's whereabouts then?!
This is looking bad...
Minions! Attack!
No! I knew it!
>The army of demons attack!

Time to fight, y'all!
Devil Download!
This army... Did Vritra muster it just to take down Indra...?
Huh? This wench...
She is one of Indra's servants...!
Bring her to me! She is to be executed in front of Vritra!
*Roar*
What?!
Saara!
>The demons kidnap Saara!
Shit! Yo, we gotta free her!

*Laugh*
From all of us?
*Wince*
*Shriek*
Damn... There's too many of 'em!
>You hear Saara's voice coming from within the army.
You don't need me to deal with Vritra...!
I was tasked with bringing you here to do just that!
For now, please, run!
Yo, we ain't gonna leave you like this!
Yeah! We're gonna get you back, Saara!
Exactly! Please don't say things like that, Saara!
Let's do this, [sys user_name]. We're gonna break through one of their weak spots!
Leave it to me!
Let's do this!
Hah!
*Scream*
Nicely done, [sys user_name].
But there's still plenty more of them left!
Aight, we're goin' in too!
Y-Yeah!
Saara, we're coming to save you!
*Pant*
*Groan*
No, to think that we would all be defeated...

*Groan*
I must warn Vritra...
>The army collapses...
Saara! Are you okay?! Did they hurt you?!
Y-Yes, I'm okay...
More importantly, are you all okay...?
>Your clothes are all torn and covered in holes.
This is nothing. We're just glad that you're safe.
Ain't that the truth. Yo, it's our job to protect regular people.
The strong protect the weak! That is what heroes do!
When did we become heroes...?
I don't know what I would've done if you got hurt, Saara!
But we got you back and everything is all good now!
Everyone...
There is something I need to tell you.
What's up?
I did not plan on revealing this to any humans.
But you went through so much to save me.
I cannot hide this from you any longer.
>Saara begins to glow.
Huh? It's too bright...
Wait, Saara...? How did you transform like that...?
I am Apsaras, a water nymph.
I sought your aid by disguising myself as a human on behalf of my master, Indra.
Yo, the weather girl that everyone loves is a demon...?
Apsaras?! I don't believe it... You're even prettier than before!
I don't believe it either...
And your "superior" is Indra... Talk about a curveball...
That means your "network of friends" is a network of demons, yes...?
Yes, that is correct.
But I must thank you again for saving me.
Oh, you don't need to do that.
But why did you choose to become a weather reporter...?
If I became a random stranger, I doubt you would have heard me out.
That is why I chose to appear on TV.
As a water nymph, I know when it will or will not rain.
Forecasting the weather seemed like a perfect fit...
I also needed time to figure out where Vritra was.
Areas undergoing severe droughts are where Vritra usually appear...
The reports I received were instrumental in finding him.
Yeah... You were pretty before...
But you're even prettier as a demon!
Thank you, young demon user.
Anyways, you were leading us to Vritra?
Yes. Being a water nymph gives me an affinity for bodies of water.
But dams are different. I feel the water moving through them.
And Vritra must be the one absorbing that water.
He must be further ahead...
No, he is approaching us...?!
Ah, so you are the ones that are here to face me...
>The air trembles as a furious voice thunders and booms.
Is that...?
Yes, the one behind this drought. Vritra...!
